ket. They were interested primarily in fixing two problems in the 801 design:","wiki"),("logic","5","A ___ gate is an idealized or physical electronic device implementing a Boolean function, a ___al operation performed on one or more binary inputs that produces a single binary output. Depending on the context, the term may refer to an ideal ___ gate, one that has for instance zero rise time and unlimited fan-out, or it may refer to a non-ideal physical device .","wiki"),("array","5","A gate ___ is an approach to the design and manufacture of application-specific integrated circuits  according to a custom order by adding metal interconnect layers in the factory.","wiki"),("forms","5","Oracle ___ is a software product for creating screens that interact with an  Oracle database.  It has an  IDE including an object navigator, property sheet and code editor that uses PL/SQL.  It was originally developed to run server-side in character mode terminal sessions.  It was ported to other plat___, including Windows, to function in a client–server environment. Later versions were ported to Java where it runs in a Java EE container and can integrate with Java and web services.","wiki"),("codec","5","A ___ is a device or computer program which encodes or decodes a digital data stream or signal.","wiki"),("gedit","5","___ ","wiki"),("pango","5","The name ___ comes from Greek pan .","wiki"),("dconf","5","___ is a low-level configuration system and settings management tool. Its main purpose is to provide a back end to GSettings on platforms that don't already have configuration storage systems. It depends on GLib. It is part of GNOME 3 and is a replacement for GConf.","wiki"),("disks","5","GNOME ___ is a graphical front-end for u___ included in the 'gnome-disk-utility' package. An introduction is included in the GNOME Documentation Project.","wiki"),("files","5","Nautilus can display previews of ___ in their icons, be they text ___, images, sound or video ___ via thumbnailers such as